items.sentence: Tom wanted to hang out with Mary and her friends.
Tom won't likely do that unless Mary asks him to.
The initial excitement Tom felt quickly wore off.
Tom probably isn't going to pass the examination.
Tom probably isn't going to tell Mary he's sorry.
Tom probably isn't going to volunteer to do that.
Tom is probably not going to be safe where he is.
Tom is probably not going to do that again today.
Tom is probably not going to do that next Monday.
Tom is probably not going to have fun doing that.
